fields.location: Museum of Childhood, Creativity Gallery, case 11
fields.public_access_description:
David Plagerson has been a full-time toymaker since 1977. He is based in Cornwall and although the Noah’s Ark sets are his main work, his range also includes pull-along animals, carousels, circuses and farm sets. In 1985, David Plagerson was awarded the British Toymakers’ Guild Cup.

Noah’s Ark  Set
This was made of handcarved and painted wood in 1978 by David Plagerson. IT was commissioned by the Museum and inspired by the 19th century German arks on display in case T8. David Plagerson’s ark sets can be bought ready painted like this example or unpainted with a beeswax finish. The Polka Children’s Theatre gave the set the ‘Children’s Toy of the Year’ award in 1979.
